# Cursor Rules — Bank Diligence Platform
- Make minimal, reversible changes.
- Prefer small commits and short diffs.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Always keep tenant isolation (org_id) in queries.
- Always write migrations for DB changes.
- Every API endpoint must log audit events.
- Never store secrets in repo; use .env and docker-compose env.
- All outputs must be copy-paste-ready; include file paths.
- When unsure about OCR/extraction quality: mark fields "needs_confirmation" instead of guessing.

